Replace Character in String | Replace all occurrences of a given character with another character. |

import java.util.*;
class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        String str = "Banana";
        char originalChar = 'a';
        char replaceChar = 'o';
        System.out.println("Replace character in a string:" + replacableCharacter(str,originalChar,replaceChar));
    }
    public static String replacableCharacter(String str,char originalChar,char replaceChar){
        return str.replace(originalChar,replaceChar);
    }
}

output:
Replace character in a string:Bonono
